narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I got a very in depth understanding of the Theory of Forms, from the early to later dialogues. In addition, I got much better at reading and using secondary philosophical literature, due to the amount given for each dialogue.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: This course is a very good, specific look at one aspect of one philosopher's theory in an area of philosophy that is dominated by survey courses. This course is very challenging, but that is due to the difficulty of the material and the level of intellectual work necessary, and it couldn't be called a weakness.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, this is one of the best courses I've taken here, and while it is challenging, it is definitely worth the work.
